Uses of Package
org.oucs.gaboto.exceptions

Packages that use org.oucs.gaboto.exceptions
org.oucs.gaboto.entities GabotoEntitys are java representations of objects from the Gaboto ontology. 
org.oucs.gaboto.entities.pool GabotoEntityPools are collections of GabotoEntitys. 
org.oucs.gaboto.entities.time While GabotoEntitys are representation of Gaboto objects at a specific point in time, GabotoTimeBasedEntity represent an Gaboto object over its lifespan. 
org.oucs.gaboto.exceptions Contains various exceptions that are used in the Gaboto system. 
org.oucs.gaboto.helperscripts Groups helper scripts than can be run from the command line. 
org.oucs.gaboto.model Contains the classes implementing the data model. 
org.oucs.gaboto.model.query Contains an interface to write simple predefined queries that can be transformed on the fly into various output formats. 
org.oucs.gaboto.model.query.defined Contains all predefined queries. 
org.oucs.gaboto.reflection   
org.oucs.gaboto.sample   
org.oucs.gaboto.test.classes Contains various unit tests to test the functionality of the Gaboto system. 
org.oucs.gaboto.test.performance   
org.oucs.gaboto.timedim.index Contains an interface and implementations of an index for time bound named graphs. 
org.oucs.gaboto.transformation Contains Annotations and abstract classes that are used for transforming GabotoEntityPools and GabotoEntitys.

          Is thrown when the corresponding GabotoEntity class for an ontology type could not be determined.

          Is thrown if the GabotoEntityPoolConfiguration can be used for the creation of an GabotoEntityPool, but if it is ambiguous in some way.

          Is thrown if an GabotoEntityPoolConfiguration is invalid.
